Much of the older apartments are built in the late 1980s and early 1990s while the newer ones are constructed from the late 90s till present.

Local farmers grew crops, primarily corn, on the "quite rural looking" areas on the Northern skirt, and originally using a creek which flows from East to Southwest as a source of irrigation until pollution took over in the late 1990s.
